rComments: The best instructor I've ever met in my entire life. Attending his class is fun.

Took MAT240 with Eckhard Meinrenken last fall, he had to leave for a week or two to attend a conference so we were left with a postdoc Peter Crooks for the weeks. Before he left, we were given the heads up that Dr. Crooks might be a better lecturer than our actual course instructor. And oh boy did he surpass all expectations. He is a LEGEND.

He is just an amazing lecturer. I've never met any other math prof ( in fact, in entire uni) who can teach difficult contents so much easier to understand. The only thing was that the final was pretty tough. I recommend acing the term tests.

rComments: I'm pretty sure the only reason I got such a good mark in his class was due to his refined, orderly, and clear method of teaching. He starts off by introducing a theorem, starts off by solving simple examples, and then generalizes the knowledge to be used in more difficult concepts.
Best prof ever.
Peter Crooks is an AMAZING instructor. Love his super clear teaching style. He makes MAT224 a lot easier to get an A. Love him.
best prof for math forever

He made MAT224 so easy to understand and enjoyable. He has his own notes and examples so you don't really need the textbook if you attend the classes. You do need to review MAT223 stuff because he tends to skip some of the computations in his examples. Tests are easy if you read the notes. 10/10 would recommend!!

rComments: Peter Crooks is definitely the best mathematics professor I have had in my academic career so far. His lectures are super clear and well-structured. For this class, his tests follow the same structure as his lectures. He uses lots of examples and he gives great feedback on any questions that students have. He has the enthusiasm and enjoys teaching.

Peter is an amazing Professor.  I wish he could just teach all my math classes.
He is amazing. You probably won't find another u of t math professor is as clear as him.
Great Prof
absolutely great lecturer! love him!

Amazing professor. Covers every topic on the test with extreme clarity and is one of the only math profs that speaks perfect grammatical english. Expect to WORK YOUR ASS OFF in this course not because of the professor, but because the course itself will make you want to cry.. good learning experience though
Enthusiastic and inspirational. Switched from physics to math because of him. Really hope he teaches mat327  in summer 2017 when I'll be taking it.
Peter is the best professor whom I have ever seen in U of T. His handwriting is so clear that you could even see it at the back of the classroom. His voice is sweet and clear. I love his class.

I honestly loved Peter! He is hands down my favourite prof this semester. He is such a nerd and I love it! I love his jokes. Time goes by very fast in his lectures. His notes are VERY organized and easy to follow when studying. Very clear. Such an approachable guy. Because he is a phD student, I felt like he was more of a friend rather than a prof.

Peter is so charming! He's obviously very passionate about Math, and it shows! He makes this class enjoyable and the time flies by. He cracks little jokes, and makes sure people have understood the material before he moves on. When people ask questions, he answers them clearly, and if there is still confusion he is happy to answer after class.
Nerdiest person I've ever seen in my entire life. Great prof.

He uses the board well and keeps everyone engaged in a 3 hour night lecture. The concepts were clear and he went through good examples in class. He is very helpful when it comes to missed lectures. Attend every class to get a good mark. Highly recommended.

Peter Crooks (PC) master race! This man is the most brilliant math lecturer I have ever had. Pretty much the stereotypical math nerd, he always makes sure the entire class understands key concepts before continuing and always dedicates a lot of time to students who are unsure and have questions.
